==English==
===Etymology===
Arabic {{ARchar|السرّة الفرس}} (''as-surra al-faras'') ‘the horse's navel’ (referring to Pegasus), from {{ARchar|[[سرة]]}} ‘navel’ + {{ARchar|[[فرس]]}} ‘horse, steed’.

===Noun===
'''Alpheratz'''
# a [[binary star]] in the [[constellation]] of [[Andromeda]] (formerly seen as part of [[Pegasus]])

===Synonyms===
*[[Alpha Andromedae]]
*[[Sirrah]]
*[[Delta Pegasi]] ''(historic)''

